With one accord they cried, "Let Him be crucified.  {SJ 134.10}  
     "And the governor said, Why, what evil hath He done?  {SJ 134.11}  
     "But they cried out the more, saying, Let Him be crucified." Matthew 27:22, 23.  {SJ 134.12}  
     Pilate's cheek paled as he heard the terrible cry, "Let 
                                                                           135
Him be crucified." He had not thought it would come to that. He had repeatedly pronounced Jesus innocent, and yet the people were determined that He should suffer this most terrible and dreaded death. Again he asked the question:  {SJ 134.13}  
     "Why, what evil hath He done?"
